commText: Sam Curran and Prabhsimran are at the crease. Sam Curran is on strike. Gerald Coetzee will open the attack

Gerald Coetzee to Sam Curran, FOUR, cracking shot, back of a length and well wide of off - Curran stands tall and then pun ches it into the gap wide of cover-point, the timing is crisp and the ball runs away to the ropes
Coetzee is bowling from round the wicket, a slip in place
Gerald Coetzee to Sam Curran, 5 wides, that's a horrendous delivery, short and way down leg, goes with the angle and gives Ishan Kishan no chance, runs away to the ropes for five wides

Gerald Coetzee to Sam Curran, leg byes, 1 run, short of a good length and at the body, Curran was looking to tuck and missed, dropped off the body and rolled to the on-side, they're through for a leg-bye
Gerald Coetzee to Prabhsimran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Gerald Coetzee to Prabhsimran, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! A first-ball duck for Prabhsimran and Coetzee celebrates, but this is Ishan Kishan's wicket, he dived full length and held on to a sharp catch. Banged in short and down leg, Prabhsimran was looking to help it on its way with the pull, the ball catches a faint inside edge and Kishan does the rest. Much needed for MI, they needed early wickets and they've got one. Prabhsimran c Ishan Kishan b Gerald Coetzee 0(1)
Rilee Rossouw, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Gerald Coetzee to Rossouw, 1 run, a direct hit and Rossouw could've been struggling, he'd have been short had Hardik made a direct hit - punched to his right at mid-off and it was Rossouw's call, not a great one and even his dive wouldn't have helped
Gerald Coetzee to Sam Curran, 1 run, fuller length delivery and well wide of off, sliced away backward of square on the off-side for a single
Gerald Coetzee to Rossouw, no run, short of a good length and at the stumps, defended back at the bowler
Jasprit Bumrah, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Bumrah to Sam Curran, no run, back of a length and just outside off, Curran stays back and defends it to the off-side
A slip in place for Bumrah
Bumrah to Sam Curran, no run, full and at the pads, Curran was shaping for the flick and missed, rolled to the off-side
Bumrah to Sam Curran, 1 run, on a length and just outside off, Curran plays with soft hands and drops it in front of short cover, calls his partner across for a single
Bumrah to Rossouw, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Bumrah to Rossouw, out Bowled!! That's an absolute screamer and poor Rossouw had no chance - full and swinging back in late, he's all over the place as he looked to drive, the feet was cemented to the crease, beaten for pace, beaten for swing and the off-stump takes a hammering. Bumrah is chuffed to bits and this is an excellent start from the Mumbai Indians. Rossouw b Bumrah 1(3)
Liam Livingstone, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Bumrah to Livingstone, 1 run, Bumrah attempts another inswinging yorker, but this is a low full-toss and it's squeezed behind square on the off-side for a single
Bumrah to Sam Curran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bumrah to Sam Curran, out Caught by Ishan Kishan!! Fuller length delivery and slipping down leg, past Sam Curran's flick and through to the keeper. But Bumrah reckons that it clipped something on its way and they've reviewed the wide call. Need UltraEdge and there's a big spike when the ball is next to the bat. Curran has been strangled down leg and PBKS have slipped early - a cheap wicket, but Bumrah will not be unhappy, was full and down leg, Curran was looking to flick and got a thin edge, was called as a wide, but Bumrah was convinced and Hardik called for the review, which did vindicate Bumrah's faith. Sam Curran c Ishan Kishan b Bumrah 6(7) [4s-1]
PBKS have called for the impact sub - Harpreet Bhatia replaces Arshdeep
Harpreet Singh Bhatia, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Gerald Coetzee to Livingstone, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!

Gerald Coetzee to Livingstone, out Caught&Bowled!! It's going from bad to worse for PBKS - banged in short and just outside off, Livingstone was undone by Coetzee's pace and he's very late on the pull, hit high on the bat and lobbed back at the bowler, Coetzee sliding forward and completing a simple catch - it's 14 for 4 and PBKS are in a big hole. Livingstone c and b Gerald Coetzee 1(2)
Shashank Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Gerald Coetzee to Shashank Singh, no run, short of a good length and just outside off, pushed back at the bowler
Gerald Coetzee to Shashank Singh, wide, fuller length delivery and well wide of off, swings away further and Kishan has to dive in front of first slip to save further wides
Two slips in place
Gerald Coetzee to Shashank Singh, 1 run, back of a length and just outside off, Shashank runs it down towards third man for a single
Gerald Coetzee to Harpreet Singh, no run, on a good length and angling across the left-hander, punched off the back-foot to backward point

Gerald Coetzee to Harpreet Singh, 1 run, banged in short and down leg, hurried Harpreet on the pull, hit high on the bat and lobbed behind square on the on-side for a single, that was bowled at 153.6 kmph
Gerald Coetzee to Shashank Singh, FOUR, cracking shot, width on offer from Coetzee - Shashank gets on top of the bounce, uses Coetzee's pace and cracks it behind square on the off-side for a boundary
Bumrah to Harpreet Singh, no run, on a good length and in that channel just outside off, left alone

Bumrah to Harpreet Singh, FOUR, nicely played, tad too straight from Bumrah, on the pads and Harpreet helps it on its way - used the pace of Bumrah and nudged it neatly, he's off and running with a boundary

Bumrah to Harpreet Singh, no run, that was close, short of a good length and just outside off - Harpreet is caught in two minds, makes a late call to play, gets an inside edge that went perilously close to the off-stump
Bumrah to Harpreet Singh, 1 run, short and wide of off, Harpreet jabs at it awkwardly and gets a quick single as the ball rolls towards mid-on
Bumrah to Shashank Singh, wide, Bumrah loses his line and spears one well down leg, called as a wide
Bumrah to Shashank Singh, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, Shashank covers for the swing and pushes it to the left of mid-off for a single

Bumrah to Harpreet Singh, no run, that's Bumrah's special - attempted the inswinging yorker, this is a full-toss that's smashing into the leg-stump if Harpreet hadn't managed to get his left leg out of the way and squeezed an inside edge
Akash Madhwal, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Akash Madhwal to Shashank Singh, no run, beaten, on a good length and shaping away from off, has Shashank poking half-heartedly and beats him on the outside edge

Akash Madhwal to Shashank Singh, FOUR, beautifully played, pitched up by Madhwal - Shashank walks forward, meets the ball on top of the bounce and then punches it over cover, almost went all the way, bouncing in front of the ropes
Akash Madhwal to Shashank Singh, no run, short and wide of off, Shashank threw his hands on the cut and missed
Akash Madhwal to Shashank Singh, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, dropped in front of cover-point for a quick single
Akash Madhwal to Harpreet Singh, 2 runs, short and angling into the left-hander, whipped behind square on the on-side where the fielder fdumbles and allows a second run

Akash Madhwal to Harpreet Singh, FOUR, streaky and four, short and wide of off - Harpreet's feet hardly moved as he threw his bat on the drive, gets a big under-edge that bounces past the stumps and beats Bumrah at short fine
Hardik Pandya, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Hardik Pandya to Shashank Singh, no run, on a good length and following Shashank as he backed away, defended back at the bowler
Hardik Pandya to Shashank Singh, 1 run, tad fuller and just outside off, dropped to the off-side and he's off for a quick single
Hardik Pandya to Harpreet Singh, no run, on a length and angling back into the left-hander, tucked to the on-side
Bumrah is off the field after his two-over burst

Hardik Pandya to Harpreet Singh, no run, a leading edge, but the ball drops well in front of cover - Harpreet was looking to work a length ball to the on-side, closed the face of the bat early and the ball popped up
Hardik, back to over the wicket
Hardik Pandya to Harpreet Singh, no run, fuller length delivery and angling into the left-hander, Harpreet loses his balance as he drives it to mid-on
Hardik Pandya to Harpreet Singh, no run, on a good length and just outside off, Harpreet plays with soft hands and defends it back at the bowler

Powerplay summary -- MI pacers rip PBKS apart -- Prabhsimran gone for a duck (0.3) -- Rossouw cleaned up by Bumrah for 1 (1.4) -- Curran dismissed by Bumrah for 6 (1.6) -- Livingstone caught and bowled off Coetzee (2.1)
Time for spin and it's Shreyas Gopal
Shreyas Gopal, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Shreyas Gopal to Shashank Singh, SIX, clubbed, a rank long hop and Shashank doesn't miss out, swivels across, picks the length and swings it into the stands at mid-wicket
Shreyas Gopal to Shashank Singh, 1 run, tossed up and sliding onto the pads, nudged behind square on the on-side for a single
Pacers in Powerplay in Mullanpur this IPL 46 overs 14 wkts Avg 24.21 SR 19.7 ER 7.37
Shreyas Gopal to Harpreet Singh, 1 run, flatter and on off, punched down to long-on for a single
Shreyas Gopal to Shashank Singh, 1 run, tossed up well wide of off, pushed into the gap wide of cover for a single
Shreyas Gopal to Harpreet Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught&Bowled!!

Shreyas Gopal to Harpreet Singh, out Caught&Bowled!! That's a superb return catch and PBKS have lost half their side now - dropped short and just outside off - Harpreet picked the length early as he went onto the back-foot, but he can't keep the punch down, went low and to the left of Shreyas who dives and pouches a clean two-handed catch. The leg-spinner breaking a partnership which was beginning to steady this chase. Harpreet Singh c and b Shreyas Gopal 13(15) [4s-2]
Jitesh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Shreyas Gopal to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, the wrong 'un, spotted by Jitesh as he drove it to long-off for a single
Lowest aggregate by PBKS top four in an IPL match 8 vs PWI Mumbai DYP 2011 8 vs MI Mullanpur 2024 * 10 vs DC Delhi 2015 14 vs DC Dharamsla 2012
Hardik Pandya to Jitesh Sharma, no run, banged in short outside off, left alone
Hardik Pandya to Jitesh Sharma, wide, another bouncer, Jitesh ducks and it's a wide for height
Hardik Pandya to Jitesh Sharma, no run, back of a length around off, 140.7kph, Jitesh hangs back and defends to backward point
Hardik Pandya to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, back of a length on middle, 136.9kph, Jitesh hangs back and tucks it behind square
Hardik Pandya to Shashank Singh, wide, short of length delivery down leg, Shashank looks to pull but is beaten
Hardik Pandya to Shashank Singh, wide, another wide down the leg-side
Hardik Pandya to Shashank Singh, 1 run, 131.9kph good length ball on middle and leg, Shashank makes some room and punches on the up to mid-off
Hardik Pandya to Jitesh Sharma, FOUR, full delivery on leg stump, Jitesh makes room, looks to go inside-out and slices it over extra cover
Hardik Pandya to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, back of a length on off, 132.2kph, Jitesh hangs back and tucks it through midwicket
Hardik looks in some discomfort. He's on his haunches and the umpire comes over to check on him. Meanwhile, there are some issues with footholes and groundstaff are looking to sort it out
Shreyas Gopal to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, length ball on middle and leg, Jitesh gets on one knee and sweeps to long leg
Shreyas Gopal to Shashank Singh, SIX, too full from Gopal, right in the slot and gets pumped down the ground! Clean strike from Shashank for six
Shreyas Gopal to Shashank Singh, SIX, six more! Slightly short on off, he pulls hard and gets it wide of long-on. Hits the cushions on the full
Shreyas Gopal to Shashank Singh, 1 run, flat outside off, back of a length, Shashank punches it to long-off
Shreyas Gopal to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, flat length ball on off, Jitesh punches off the back foot to long-off
PBKS top five aggregate in last four matches 78(63) vs GT 75(69) vs SRH 75(79) vs RR 21(28) vs MI
Shreyas Gopal to Shashank Singh, 1 run, flat length ball on middle, Shashank tucks it through midwicket
Timeout! Good partnership between these two so far but they need to take it much deeper to have any chance. Most of the batting has already been blown away
Akash Madhwal [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack

Akash Madhwal to Shashank Singh, 1 run, driven powerfully to the left of Madhwal who sticks his hand out but can't hold on to the catch. Those ones either stick or they don't. This one hasn't, and it has hurt Madhwal as well. Physio is out to tend to him
Misses a full toss and is given out LBW. The ball tailed in slightly, went past the inside edge and thudded onto the front pad. Jitesh has reviewed. Ball-tracking says it would've clipped leg stump.
Akash Madhwal to Jitesh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Akash Madhwal to Jitesh Sharma, out Lbw!! Misses a full toss and is given out LBW. The ball tailed in late from Madhwal, went past the inside edge and thudded onto the front pad. Jitesh has reviewed. Ball-tracking says it would've clipped leg stump. Jitesh Sharma lbw b Akash Madhwal 9(9) [4s-1]
Ashutosh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Akash Madhwal to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, 137.7kph yorker just outside off, Ashutosh squeezes it wide of point
Akash Madhwal to Shashank Singh, 1 run, length ball on off, Shashank hangs back and works it to long-on
Akash Madhwal to Ashutosh Sharma, SIX, length ball straying a long way down leg, Ashutosh swings hard and sends it sailing over the fine leg boundary
Akash Madhwal to Ashutosh Sharma, 2 runs, full toss on off, Ashutosh gets forward and drives nicely through cover. Gets back for two as Romario cuts it off in the deep
Romario Shepherd, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Shepherd to Shashank Singh, 1 run, short of length outside off, slower one, Shashank steps out and swats it to deep midwicket
Is there some issue with Hardik? He looked in discomfort after his previous over, and hasn't bowled after that. They've opted for Romario instead
Shepherd to Ashutosh Sharma, FOUR, short of length outside off, plenty of width and Ashutosh slaps it to the point boundary
Shepherd to Ashutosh Sharma, 2 runs, length ball outside off, slower one, Ashutosh taps it gently through point and gets back for two
Shepherd to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, fuller than a length outside off, driven hard but straight to extra cover
Shepherd to Ashutosh Sharma, SIX, back of a length around the waist, Ashutosh pulls it with a helicopter flourish and just about clears deep square leg
Shepherd to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, short of length outside off, slower one, Ashutosh looks to cut but is beaten
Hardik coming on to bowl again. So there's no real injury concern which is good to see
Hardik Pandya [2.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Hardik Pandya to Shashank Singh, 1 run, full at the stumps, slower one, and Shashank drives to long-on
Hardik Pandya to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, length ball just outside off, slower one, Ashutosh hangs back and taps it wide of point
Hardik Pandya to Shashank Singh, 1 run, back of a length on off, Shashank advances and tucks it through midwicket

Hardik Pandya to Ashutosh Sharma, SIX, slower length ball straying down leg, Ashutosh bends his knees and repeats that helicopter pull which he pulled off in the previous over as well. He whips it over short fine and clears the ropes too
Hardik Pandya to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, backs away to the leg-side and again goes for the same shot as Hardik follows him. Length isn't short enough this time and he's hit on the thigh
Hardik Pandya to Shashank Singh, 1 run, full outside off, slower one, Shashank steers it to short third
Bumrah brought back after some costly overs. Required rate is still very manageable. It's the six wickets they've lost that's the problem.
Jasprit Bumrah [2.0-0-9-2] is back into the attack
Bumrah to Shashank Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Bumrah to Shashank Singh, out Caught by Tilak Varma!! Well there you go. Any signs of trouble, go to Bumrah. He's the best in the tournament, best in the format, best in the world, out of the world. Slower ball floated up on off, Shashank is totally deceived as he goes for the lofted shot and chips it straight up in the air. Easy catch for Tilak coming in from midwicket. Shashank Singh c Tilak Varma b Bumrah 41(25) [4s-2 6s-3]
Harpreet Brar, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Bumrah to Harpreet Brar, no run, banged in short, Brar ducks
Bumrah to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, close to the blockhole on off, Brar squeezes it to mid-on
Shashank - Ashutosh partnerships 43(22) 66*(27) 34(17)
Bumrah to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, full and straight, driven back to Bumrah
Bumrah to Ashutosh Sharma, no ball, back of a length outside off, slower one, Ashutosh waits in the crease and dabs it to backward point. Oh Bumrah has overstepped

Bumrah to Ashutosh Sharma, SIX, Ashutosh has a big smile on his face as he gets down low and sweeps Bumrah for six off the free hit. Something to remember and tell your grandchildren about. Bumrah goes for the yorker but Ashutosh manages to take it on the full
Bumrah to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, back of a length on off, blocked into the off-side
Romario Shepherd [1.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack

Over Summary (7-13) * Punjab lose their 5th wicket as Harpreet falls for 13 * Hardik Padya concedes 10 runs in the 8th over * Shreyas Gopal goes for 16 runs in the 9th over with Shashank hitting him for back-to-back sixes * Jitesh Sharma trapped in front by Akash Madhwal for 9 * Ashutosh Sharma gets going with a massive six off Madhwal * Romario Shephard concedes 13 runs in the 11th over * Bumrah comes back to the attack, dismisses Shashank Singh for 41
Shepherd to Ashutosh Sharma, SIX, Ashutosh playing a blinder out there. Back of a length, slower ball that sits up around the waist and he wallops the pull over midwicket
Shepherd to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, overpitched on off, Ashutosh pushes it to mid-off
Shepherd to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, full toss on leg, Ashutosh punches it to long-on
Shepherd to Harpreet Brar, no run, back of a length delivery slanted in on middle, Brar blocks from the crease

Shepherd to Harpreet Brar, leg byes, 1 run, length ball slanted in from round the wicket, Brar looks to slog but it goes off his back pad into the off-side. There's a direct hit at the non-striker's end but Brar is safely home
100+ runs in an IPL season batting #8 or below \n138* Ashutosh Sharma in 2024 \n115 Rashid Khan in 2023
Shepherd to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, very full around off, Ashutosh looks to hammer it through extra cover but finds the fielder
Gerald Coetzee [2.0-0-18-2] is back into the attack

Gerald Coetzee to Harpreet Brar, FOUR, both ends will need to contribute if PBKS are to get closer, and this shot will raise some hope. Full outside off, Brar drives sweetly and hits it over extra cover
Gerald Coetzee to Harpreet Brar, FOUR, lucky runs! Full outside off, Brar doesn't move his feet as he goes for the drive and it runs away off the outside edge

Gerald Coetzee to Harpreet Brar, no run, Coetzee drops a fairly simple return catch! Just didn't pick it up soon enough. Short of length at the body, rushes onto Brar who's late on the pull and it loops up off the splice. Coetzee bends down in followthrough and goes one-handed, but fails to hold on
Gerald Coetzee to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, pulled down to fine leg
All four fielders on the leg-side are at the boundary, no one in the ring. Coetzee from round the wicket
Gerald Coetzee to Ashutosh Sharma, FOUR, Coetzee bowls a full toss down leg, Ashutosh swings and gets it away fine. Absolutely races off the bat to the boundary
Gerald Coetzee to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, slower length ball outside off as he switches back to over the wicket, Ashutosh looks to cut but misses
Akash Madhwal [2.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack
Akash Madhwal to Harpreet Brar, wide, wide yorker outside off, Brar fails to reach it and it's called wide
Akash Madhwal to Harpreet Brar, no run, another wide yorker, this one's inside the marker, and Brar swings and misses
Akash Madhwal to Harpreet Brar, wide, Madhwal sticking to the wide yorker, but this is just outside the marker
Akash Madhwal to Harpreet Brar, leg byes, 1 run, Brar anticipates the wide yorker, walks across for the scoop but is hit on the pad
Madhwal stays round the wicket for Ashutosh as well
Akash Madhwal to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, cracking yorker on leg stump, Ashutosh can only squeeze it back down the pitch

Akash Madhwal to Ashutosh Sharma, no ball, SIX, speared over mid-off to bring up a blistering fifty! The crowd roars in applause, and that roar gets louder as the no-ball siren goes off. Madhwal has overstepped. It's an attempted yorker on leg stump, falls short of the mark, Ashutosh makes room and drills it over mid-off

Akash Madhwal to Ashutosh Sharma, SIX, Ashutosh Sharma, you beauty! Plays the reverse-scoop over short third and it sails over the ropes. Another attempted yorker on leg stump, he gets into position and executes flawlessly
Akash Madhwal to Ashutosh Sharma, wide, straying down leg, wide called
Crowd chanting "Ashu, Ashu"
Akash Madhwal to Ashutosh Sharma, leg byes, 1 run, skiddy length ball slanted in around leg, cramps Ashutosh on the slog and strikes him on the pad

Akash Madhwal to Harpreet Brar, SIX, what is happening! This game seemed gone a short while ago, and now PBKS need just 28 off the last four overs. Full delivery on off, right in the slot for Brar and he launches it a long way down the ground. Crowd is going berserk

Timeout! Much needed break for MI who have been left stunned by this onslaught. Ashutosh Sharma has played an absolute blinder to turn the game out of nowhere. MI have one precious over of Bumrah left and they will need him to strike. Here he is.
Jasprit Bumrah [3.0-0-18-3] is back into the attack
Bumrah to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, full delivery outside off, slower one, Ashutosh gets forward and knocks it to extra cover for a single

Bumrah to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, oh dear. Brar has absolutely no clue as a fiery bumper comes his way. He tries to duck while leaving his hands up there, and gets rapped on the glove. Looks to be in pain, but he's okay to continue
Bumrah to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, short outside off, Ashutosh ramps it fine but deep third is placed fine as well. Coetzee tumbles but cuts it off
Bumrah to Harpreet Brar, no run, bouncer from round the wicket, Brar ducks under it
Bumrah to Harpreet Brar, no run, banged in short outside off, Brar looks to cut but is beaten

Bumrah to Harpreet Brar, no run, 141kph short of length delivery on off, Brar gets on top of the bounce and fends it down the pitch. Just three off the over, but no wickets lost and Bumrah has been successfully seen off
Hardik waving his arms around to get his fielders in position. Coetzee has the ball.
Gerald Coetzee [3.0-0-31-2] is back into the attack
Gerald Coetzee to Ashutosh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Gerald Coetzee to Ashutosh Sharma, out Caught by Nabi!! Coetzee almost explodes in celebration as Ashutosh holes out in the deep. Short of length outside off, slower one, he pulls it in the air and it goes straight to deep midwicket. A terrific knock comes to an end. Ashutosh Sharma c Nabi b Gerald Coetzee 61(28) [4s-2 6s-7]
Harshal Patel, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Gerald Coetzee to Harshal Patel, 1 run, length ball on off, driven to extra cover
Gerald Coetzee to Harpreet Brar, Leg byes 1 run, back of a length delivery slanted in on middle and leg, Brar looks to pull but is struck on the thigh
Gerald Coetzee to Harshal Patel, no run, short outside off, Harshal slashes but misses
Gerald Coetzee to Harshal Patel, no run, another sharp bouncer outside off, Harshal tries to upper-cut but misses again. Was that over the head? Umpire doesn't think so

50+ scores batting #8 or below in IPL 79* Rashid Khan GT v MI 2023 66* P Cummins KKR v CSK 2021 64* A Russell KKR v SRH 2024 64 Harbhajan MI v PBKS 2015 61 Ashutosh Sharma PBKS v MI 2024 52* C Morris DC v MI 2017
Gerald Coetzee to Harshal Patel, no run, slower short ball around off, Harshal is cramped for room as he looks to cut and gets beaten again

Hardik to bowl the penultimate over. A substitute is on the field for MI and the umpire walks up to him for some clarification. Not sure what's going on. Is it Coetzee who's off the field? No it's Gopal. But he has to come back on again. There's a penalty as well for slow over-rate - Mumbai need to have 5 players inside the ring for the last two overs
Hardik Pandya [3.0-0-22-0] is back into the attack
Hardik Pandya to Harpreet Brar, 2 runs, back of a length on leg, Brar is cramped for room and he mistimes it wide of long-on

Hardik Pandya to Harpreet Brar, no run, full delivery just outside leg, Brar walks across the stumps looking to flick but misses. Wide is not given, and Brar reviews. However, the third umpire finds that he has moved across significantly, so it remains non-wide. Would've hit the pad had he not moved
Hardik Pandya to Harpreet Brar, 2 runs, no one protecting the boundary on the off-side, so Brar backs away, gets a full ball and slices it over point. The fielder chases it down from point
Hardik Pandya to Harpreet Brar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Hardik Pandya to Harpreet Brar, out Caught by Nabi!! Flicked in the air, Nabi settles under it and grabs it comfortably. Brar falls as well. The ball was there to be put away. Length ball on the pads, he whips it behind square but doesn't get enough on it. Easy catch at long leg. Harpreet Brar c Nabi b Hardik Pandya 21(20) [4s-2 6s-1]
Kagiso Rabada, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Hardik Pandya to Rabada, SIX, PBKS just refuse to lie down. Rabada walks out and nails his first ball for six. Short of length at the body, he swings hard and pulls it all the way over deep backward square
Fine leg and third are both in the ring
Hardik Pandya to Rabada, 1 run, slower ball floated up at the stumps, Rabada clears the front leg and drives to long-on

MI having a conference in the middle with 5-6 players involved. Bumrah, Rohit, Hardik, the bowler Madhwal among others. Long discussions about the field, and what to do. Now Bumrah goes to Kishan, while another group of three MI players gathers somewhere else. Rabada is watching all this patiently as the fielders move across here and there. Mid-off and extra cover are in the circle. Madhwal to bowl from round the wicket
Akash Madhwal [3.0-0-44-1] is back into the attack
Akash Madhwal to Rabada, wide, goes for a wide yorker but fails to keep it inside the marker
Rabada is in trouble. He is struggling on the second run, the throw comes in flat and Kishan breaks the stumps quickly. This is such an anticlimax. He's well short of his ground.
Akash Madhwal to Rabada, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Akash Madhwal to Rabada, out Rabada Run Out!! 1 run completed. Rabada is in trouble. He is struggling on the second run, the throw comes in flat and Kishan breaks the stumps quickly. This is such an anticlimax. He's well short of his ground, and MI have prevented what would've been one of the great jailbreaks of the season. Wide yorker outside off, Rabada squeezes it to deep point, looks to come back for two but it's very tight and very risky. Nabi does well in the deep, and Kishan does the rest. Rabada run out (Mohammad Nabi/Ishan Kishan) 8(3) [6s-1]

23:40 Local Time, 18:10 GMT, 23:40 IST: Massive relief for MI who almost lost the plot in the face of a stunning late assault led by Ashutosh Sharma. At 77/6, having lost most of their batting, PBKS seemed dead and buried in the run-chase. But a sensational 28-ball 61 from Ashutosh brought them back out of nowhere. He played some helicopter pulls, swept Bumrah for a six, took Madhwal to the cleaners and left MI gasping for a while. But he holed out in the deep when the hosts were just 25 away from the target, and the lower-order couldn't get them over the line. Bumrah stood out again for MI, taking wickets with the new ball and then coming back to break a dangerous partnership by getting rid of Shashank Singh. He gave absolutely nothing away even when the rest were disappearing to all parts and put on a show again.

Sam Curran | PBKS captain - Another close one, I think this team likes a close one, but unfortunately another loss. Another incredible knock from the young guy (on Ashutosh), but another close loss. It's very tough, you want to lose close games rather then getting absolutely thumped, but we've lost a lot of wickets at the start, the way the younger guys have taken the team so close is heartening (on Shashank Singh and Ashutosh Sharma). They have incredible confidence, you see a guy like Ashutosh having the confidence to play the sweeps and the big hits against pacers, it's so great to watch them in action. It's disheartening to lose close games, but there are a lot of positives in this team. We still have the belief in us, we believe we can turn this around, the sun will come up tomorrow and we will hopefully get on a winning run.

Gerald Coetzee: What a game! We got a good total on the board, we started really well (with the ball), we thought we had it.. cricket is a funny game and they batted really well, it was like a seesaw and couldn't decide who would win the game. I saw the ball land and knew it would spin, so I got my body behind, I didn't care how I stopped it as long as I stopped it (16.3). It is incredible, it is completely different to whatever I have experienced and even the fan experience, just incredible.

Hardik, MI captain: Very good game of cricket. Everyone's nerve got tested. We did speak about before the game that the character will be checked in this game. Naturally you think you're ahead in the game. But we knew IPL has a tendency to produce these games. Unbelievable - coming in and playing like that (Ashutosh's knock). Almost every ball hitting the middle. Happy for him and chuffed for his future. We did speak in the timeout that it doesn't matter how good we look. We'll keep scrapping in this game. We were quite soft in certain overs. Nevertheless, a win is a win.

Bumrah, POTM: This was a close game. Much closer than what we thought it would go. Of course you want to make an impact when the ball does something. In this format the ball swings two overs. When I want to bowl more, I play Test cricket. That fulfills my desires. This format is a little difficult for bowlers, with time restrictions and impact player rules. Batting lineup becomes deeper and deeper. But that's not in your control. I do relay the message to the bowlers whenever I can. But you also don't want to deliver too many messages in the heat of the moment.

Two crucial points for MI on the road to lift them up in the table. What a game though. Out of nowhere Ashutosh produced that blinder and almost pulled off a heist. It wasn't to be, and Punjab Kings remain stuck close to the bottom. That's all we have. It's a goodbye from Sagar Chawla on behalf of Siva, Akshay Maanay and Pradeep Krishnamurthy.
